A rescue team from China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) arrived at Istanbul Airport in Türkiye on Thursday noon, China Media Group reported. The 59-member team will visit quake-stricken areas in Adana to assist in search and rescue operations. The team has brought 8 tonnes of equipment, including life detectors and masonry cutting machines, besides the team's daily necessities, the local government said in a notice. (Cover via China Media Group)